. Linux has VFS module called pipefs gets mounted in kernel space during boot
. pipefs is mounted alongside the root file system (/) not in it
. pipefs cannot be directly examined by the user unlike most file systems
. the entry point to pipefs is the pipe(2) syscall
. The pipe(2) syscall is used by 
